cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV. 

This paper is primarily focused on language modeling and communication, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The use of deep neural networks and continual learning also suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The evaluation of the framework through simulations and experiments suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics) categories. Finally, the use of COCO (Common Objects in Context) dataset suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category.
